column5: While looking for something else, I came across this video. It was amazing to watch! Thought I'd share...

our trips get big ones too big one at 2"40 into the video   <iframe width="960" height="720" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/WI5yM0yMBjw" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>   <embed width="600" height="361" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowFullscreen="true" allowNetworking="all" wmode="transparent" src="http://static.photobucket.com/player.swf" flashvars="file=http%3A%2F%2Fvid25.photobucket.com%2Falbums%2Fc52%2FMrbeee1954%2FVideos%2FMPEG0005.mp4">
Yeah...No fish in Temagami eh Terry? Lloyd's a small dude...makes the laker look big.
well, just no fish in Temagami for me..LOL
Never caught or even seen a trout in person, I think I heard something about a fish being 45 inches...is that true? Had no idea trout got that long
Yep they get that long. Here's a buddy holding a 50+ incher.   And of course, the mother of all laker ice fishing videos!!!

Wow! Thanks for sharing Terry! Was super fun to watch! Can't imagine the feeling...yet!  Drifter...Holy Crap!!!!! That must have been a moment! I am in complete AWE of that pic! His head is bigger then your buddy's!!!!  I really look forward to some PB's in the future! All I have is my 12" Perch! LOL!
No internet at home and work blocks utube! I wanna see, I wanna see. Haha.
